Surfaced 2026-06-09 while implementing the Introspect contract (karr #3, commit ad0cf31).

GAP
DBIO::DB2::Introspect::Columns reads syscat.columns but does NOT capture identity/generated metadata (syscat.columns.identity = 'Y', generated, etc.). So the native model columns have no is_auto_increment signal, and the new table_columns_info() contract method cannot set is_auto_increment / retrieve_on_insert. For DBIO::Generate this means generated result classes miss is_auto_increment on DB2 identity PKs.

FIX
- Add identity/generated columns to the syscat.columns SELECT in
  lib/DBIO/DB2/Introspect/Columns.pm; store e.g. is_auto_increment / generated
  in each column hash.
- In DBIO::DB2::Introspect::table_columns_info, set is_auto_increment => 1 (and
  retrieve_on_insert => 1 when the column is in the PK) from that field — cf.
  the PostgreSQL pattern ($column->{identity}).
- Extend t/40-introspect-contract.t with an identity column fixture asserting
  is_auto_increment.

MINOR (same area): t/10-db2.t and t/20-db2-core.t are byte-identical — consolidate to a single integration test.
